        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Sept. 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5611</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Dr. J Wolff</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Phi.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As I partly expected the <placeName>Syracuse</placeName> business is
                all stuff,<lb/>
                <persName>Dr. Raphael</persName> told me yesterday that he was invoked and would
                accept<lb/> I do not know what <persName>stone</persName> meant that my letter of
                the <date>14th</date> was received<lb/> but he does say what day, as on that depends
                the fairness of then proceeding.<lb/> However as I am then for, I shall push on to
                    <placeName>Boston</placeName> and there places<lb/> in the hopes of making my
                expenses in another way. <persName>Mr Stone</persName> says he<lb/> could not wait
                any longer, so he asked <persName>Dr R.</persName> I do not comprehend, how<lb/> my
                    <del>my could</del> letter was not received in due time, as I answered <add>the
                    invitation</add> at once on the<lb/> day <del>the invitation</del> it got to my
                hands.__I shall deliberate with myself today whether<lb/> to go to
                    Cleoclared<add>?</add> tomorrow or to the <placeName>East</placeName>, probably
                the latter; and if I do so<lb/> I will send word of my stopping place. By way of
                venture of any thing<lb/> requires attention you may direct to <persName>Henry
                    Herman</persName>, <placeName>24 Ann Street<lb/> Boston</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now to business. A man by name of <persName>S. Wolfe</persName>
                <placeName>Winnsboro South<lb/> Carolina</placeName> wants a set of prayer books for
                his wife. <add>?</add>
                <persName>Gaskill</persName><lb/> has sent the books home pack one set, the <hi
                    rend="underline">blue</hi> ones in a higher<lb/> little package, and direct to
                the care of <persName>S. Hart</persName> to be forwarded<lb/> to <persName>Jacob
                    Levine</persName>
                <placeName>Columbia</placeName>, and send a note to <persName>Wolfe</persName> to
                advise him<lb/> that the parcel has you proceed to his order. It would be well to
                pay<lb/> the freight and charge him with it. The steamship Albatross<lb/> sails on
                    <date>Wednesday</date>. If the books are yet at <persName>Mr
                    Gaskill's</persName> they may<lb/> be sent from there. The price of the
                    <sic>booke</sic> is 225<lb/>100, freight <add>?</add>; <add>?</add><lb/> and
                that to the Bill.__</p>
            <p rend="Note: ">Bottom right corner of page folded, partially obscuring some text.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p><persName>Mr M Pelshaw</persName>
                <placeName>347 Grand St.</placeName> wants four dozen spelling books,<lb/> please
                ask <persName>Mr Gaskill</persName> to forward them by Adams' Express, freight<lb/>
                not to be paid, as <persName>Mr P.</persName> is to do that here.__</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><add>?</add>
                <persName>Hyneman</persName> sends for a set J P. Books let him have<lb/> the plain
                calf set at <hi rend="underline">22.50</hi>. <add>?</add>
                <persName>TJ Seixas</persName> sends one on<lb/> pair here by express later charge
                of it, and if called for<lb/> the price is $21 and no less.__</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Love to all</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please forward the enclosed to <persName>Mr L. Haas</persName>,
                    <persName>M Mayer<lb/> Haas</persName> of <placeName>135 Market St</placeName>
                upstairs</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">P.S. I mean to go to <placeName>Boston</placeName><add>?</add>
                first</p>
        </body>
